ont><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=515.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question for those wanting Songs moved off Body resist...</span><hr size=1> What makes you think with Spellcrafting the way it is right now, people you fight will not have maxed energy or matter or spirit or whatever resist you move it to?<br>
<br>
Would you like Mythic to move it to a different resist and then say, there, Skalds are back at their old effectiveness and move on. Then you go out in RvR and find out people are running around with maxed whatever resist it was moved to and you're still pretty screwed.<br>
<br>
So how about just stopping asking for silly things like that (and you know if it changes for skalds, it'll change for all the other music classes as well), and ask for some changes with real meat on them.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=damthelskald@teamskald>DamthelSkald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/19/03 2:45:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=515.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Comment</span><hr size=1>  The reason I think folks want it changed is due to the fact that healer's mezz is also body, and so everyone and there brother is gona have max resist to body. If you go and change ours to a different type, that would force folks to either change there resists around. Ya wana resist a healers mezz? (which of course most would, an AE with much longer duration is a no-brainer) but at least it makes them more susceptable to our mez, helping the overall group, to a small degree. If I am way off on this correct me, but from what I have read thats what makes sense to me.<br>
<br>
  Damthel   Tristan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0a5t>t0a5t</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/19/03 2:59:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=515.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> last I checked, most SC templates can easily max needed stats (str/con/x/y/z/etc), ALL resists with just 99% qual items. So it wouldn't address the concept of resists at all.<br>
<br>
The healer mezz argument bears some merit. However, considering the Spiritmaster has Cold and Spirit based Mezz, Midgard as a whole has 3 resist table Mezzes (2 really since different resist table mezzes from the same class will not stack) already.<br>
<br>
